<HEADLINE>
TAIPEI HOSTING 2007 INTERNATIONAL KARATE INVITATIONAL
CHAMPIONSHIP
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  June  1  (CNA) 06/01/07  21:24:36 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
The 2007 Taipei International Karate Invitational Championship
will take place Saturday at the Taipei Gymnasium, with some 250
karate practitioners from seven countries competing.
</P>
<P>
The competitors, who come from the United States, the United
Kingdom, Thailand, Malaysia, India, Japan and Taiwan, will vie
for titles in the kumite and kata categories.
</P>
<P>
The event will be held in conjunction with the National Shotokan
Karate Championship.
</P>
<P>
The organizers of the two events have invited world-renowned
shotokan karate master Hirokazu Kanazawa, 77, and his son
Fumatoshi Kanazawa to the two championships.
</P>
<P>
Hirokazu Kanazawa will appear at the competition and sign books
he has written on karate for fans. The Chinese versions of two of
his books -- Stronger Karate in Six Weeks and Karate, My life --
were recently released in Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He is currently the chief instructor and president of the Japan-
based  Shotokan Karate-do  International  Federation,  an
organization he founded after he left the Japan Karate
Association in 1979.
</P>
